THIRD-PARTY ONTOLOGY ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS

DigitalSoma uses Uniform Resource Identifiers (URIs) from the following
open ontologies as property identifiers. No ontology content is bundled
with this software; URIs are used as stable identifiers only.

  Uberon Multi-Species Anatomy Ontology
    Mungall C.J. et al. (2012). Uberon, an integrative multi-species
    anatomy ontology. Genome Biology 13, R5.
    https://obofoundry.org/ontology/uberon.html
    Licence: CC BY 3.0

  SNOMED Clinical Terms (SNOMED CT)
    International Health Terminology Standards Development Organisation
    (IHTSDO). https://www.snomed.org/
    Use of SNOMED CT identifiers in open-source software is permitted
    under the SNOMED CT Affiliate Licence for non-commercial or
    open-source projects. See https://www.snomed.org/snomed-ct/get-snomed

  VeDDRA — Veterinary Dictionary for Drug Regulatory Activities
    European Medicines Agency (EMA).
    https://www.ema.europa.eu/en/veterinary-regulatory/
    Used under EMA open-data policy.

  NCBITaxon — NCBI Taxonomy Ontology
    National Center for Biotechnology Information.
    https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy
    Public domain (US Government work).

  UCUM — Unified Code for Units of Measure
    Regenstrief Institute, Inc. https://ucum.org/
    Licence: open licence for use of unit codes as identifiers.

  PATO — Phenotype and Trait Ontology
    https://obofoundry.org/ontology/pato.html
    Licence: CC BY 3.0

  HP — Human Phenotype Ontology / MP — Mammalian Phenotype Ontology
    https://hpo.jax.org / https://www.informatics.jax.org/
    Licence: hpoplus (HP), CC BY 4.0 (MP)
